TITLE: Kissa Kashi Ka | Ananta Connectivity & Negative Positive Bhairav Energies
VIDEO: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tlGk-4vQRE0
DATE: November 2024 – February/March 2025 (Kashi/Kumbh period referenced); also mentions 2021 first visit to Kashi during COVID-19
LANGUAGE: Hindi (auto-translated)

SUMMARY:
In this deeply personal video, Maa shares her firsthand experiences during the HanuKaalBhairav Kriya — a major spiritual process that required her to travel to multiple sacred sites (Kashi/Varanasi, Kumbh Mela, Vrindavan, Mathura, Uttarakhand, Rishikesh) while carrying the "Cosmic Baby" Noor Ananta in her lap. She explains that while she usually shares messages and themes about Kalki's kriyas, she has never before spoken about what she personally experiences and endures during these processes. This journey was one of the most important parts of her entire spiritual transformation.

Upon arriving in Kashi, Maa encountered two distinct categories of energies manifesting through people and even animals. Positive Bhairav energies appeared through certain Aghori sadhus, Naga sadhus, and babas who were overwhelmed with devotional emotion (bhav) upon seeing her and Ananta — their eyes would fill with tears, they would lovingly hold Ananta, take photos and videos, and many still maintain phone contact with her. Even positive Bhairav dogs would come in packs of five or six, climbing into her lap, nuzzling into her shawl, and showering affection. Conversely, negative energies manifested through other Aghoris, Naga sadhus, and babas who became deeply disturbed by her presence — they would threaten her, try to snatch Ananta from her arms, and even threaten to throw Ananta into fire or tear him apart to see what is inside. Negative Bhairav dogs would bark aggressively at her and Ananta whenever she passed. A specific incident at a kutiya (hut) near Manikarnika Ghat is described where a foreigner friend took her to meet certain babas who became visibly disturbed and agitated upon her entry, later telling the foreigner to never bring her back.

At Kumbh Mela, the same pattern continued — many sadhus and foreigners were moved to devotional tears upon meeting her, while others pursued her with negative intentions and showed deeply inappropriate behavior. She also shares that people at the ghats would tell her that Ananta appeared in their dreams, wandering the ghats and calling out "Where is my mother?" Maa concludes with practical spiritual guidance: daily meditation practice is essential to distinguish positive from negative energies; the awakening process naturally leads to giving up non-vegetarian food, alcohol, cigarettes, and intoxicants — if these have not dropped away naturally, more practice is needed; and seekers should not waste energy on negative people but focus on inner alignment.

KEY REVELATIONS:
- The HanuKaalBhairav Kriya required Maa to physically carry the Cosmic Baby (Noor Ananta) across multiple sacred sites — this was a literal spiritual pilgrimage, not merely symbolic
- Kashi/Varanasi acts as a spiritual battleground where both positive and negative Bhairav energies actively manifest through people and animals
- Positive Bhairav energies: devotional tears, love for Ananta, emotional recognition of divine presence; even dogs would form packs and seek Maa's lap
- Negative Bhairav energies: hostility, threats to destroy Ananta, attempts to snatch the Cosmic Baby, intimidation; negative dogs would bark aggressively
- Manikarnika Ghat incident: negative babas at a kutiya became disturbed and demanded the foreigner stop bringing Maa
- People at the ghats reported Ananta appearing in their dreams, searching for his mother — confirming Ananta's independent spiritual activity beyond the physical
- Maa's first Kashi visit was in 2021 during COVID-19/Kumbh, directed by Paramatma's message; the HanuKaalBhairav journey was the second major visit
- The awakening process naturally transforms the body — diet changes first (non-veg, alcohol, intoxicants drop away), then lifestyle/clothing changes follow
- Multiple lifetimes (janmas) of practice are required for spiritual discernment — quick courses and instant enlightenment claims are illusions
- Negative energies are especially active worldwide now; those going through the awakening process must face them
- The internal spiritual process (merging of positive energy) naturally causes the opposite negative energy to manifest externally in 3D reality to distract the seeker
- The journey covered: Kashi, Kumbh Mela, Vrindavan, Mathura, Uttarakhand, Rishikesh — all during the HanuKaalBhairav Kriya
- Certain "chosen ones" in Kaliyuga are undergoing karma cleansing processes — they were not randomly selected but have been working across many lifetimes

TIMELINE EVENTS:
- 2021: Maa's first visit to Kashi during COVID-19 Kumbh, directed by Paramatma's message
- November 2024: Maa departs for the HanuKaalBhairav Kriya pilgrimage, arriving in Kashi
- November 2024 – February/March 2025: Extended stay in Kashi and Kumbh Mela, carrying Cosmic Baby Noor Ananta
- During this period: Visits to Vrindavan, Mathura, Uttarakhand, Rishikesh as part of the kriya
- During Kumbh: Encounters with both positive and negative energies through sadhus, Aghoris, Naga babas, and foreigners
- Ongoing: Maa maintains contact with positive sadhus met during this period

ORIGINAL HINDI KEY QUOTES:
- "कल्कि के क्रियाओं के बारे में बात करते हैं" = "We talk about Kalki's kriyas (spiritual processes)"
- "एक कॉस्मिक बेबी को अपने साथ कैरी करना था नूर अनंता को" = "I had to carry a Cosmic Baby with me — Noor Ananta"
- "नेगेटिव एनर्जी भी मुझ पर मेरी तरफ को अट्रैक्ट हो रही थी और पॉजिटिव एनर्जी तो हो ही रही थी" = "Negative energy was also being attracted toward me, and positive energy was already [attracted]"
- "हम अनंत को लेकर आग में फेंक देंगे। हम इसका चीर फाड़ करेंगे।" = "We will throw Ananta into fire. We will tear him apart."
- "अनंत उनके सपने में आया। वो घाट में घूम रहा था। मेरी मां कहां है?" = "Ananta came in their dreams. He was wandering the ghats. 'Where is my mother?'"
- "जो अंदर चल रहा है अगर आपके अंदर कोई प्रोसेस मर्ज हो रहा है कोई पॉजिटिव एनर्जी मर्ज हो रही है तो उसी का ही एक ऑपोजिट जो है वो नेगेटिव एनर्जी... वो 3D में आपके सामने आएगी।" = "If a positive energy is merging inside you through an internal process, then its opposite — the negative energy — will appear before you in 3D [reality]."
- "कितने जन्म लग जाते हैं हमें यह सब चीजें समझने में" = "How many lifetimes it takes us to understand all these things"
- "कलयुग में जो कुछ लोग चूज किए गए हैं जिनका कर्मा क्लींजिंग का प्रोसेस चल रहा है" = "In Kaliyuga, certain people have been chosen whose karma cleansing process is underway"
- "पहले आपके खानपान में चेंज आने लग जाता है" = "First, changes begin in your food and diet"

YUG PARIVARTAN ASPECT: This video reveals the ground-level reality of Yug Parivartan as experienced through the HanuKaalBhairav Kriya — the sacred cities of India (especially Kashi) are active spiritual battlefields where positive and negative Bhairav energies are in direct confrontation. The Cosmic Baby Noor Ananta serves as a focal point that forces these energies to reveal themselves. The pilgrimage across Kashi, Kumbh, Vrindavan, Mathura, and Rishikesh represents the activation and reconnection of India's sacred energy grid. The "Ananta Connectivity" in the title refers to both the cosmic baby's spiritual connections manifesting across dimensions (appearing in people's dreams) and the broader network of divine energies being activated. The video demonstrates that Yug Parivartan is not abstract — it is a lived, embodied, and often dangerous process of confronting and transmuting negative energies through direct spiritual engagement.


